  </table><para id="eip-958">Suppose widget workers receive $10 per hour.  Multiplying the Workers row by $10 (and eliminating the blanks) gives us the cost of producing different levels of output.</para><table id="eip-236" summary="This table displays the costs of widget production based on the previous information. For each value in the previous table, the worker cost of 0 per hour is applied by multiplying. Building one widget requires 3.25 workers. At 0 per hour, the cost is >2.50. Two widgets requires 4.4 workers, which costs $44. Three widgets requires 5.2 workers, which costs $52. And four widgets requires 9 workers, and costs $90.">
